cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.NE, cs.SY. 

The paper discusses optimization problems in Machine Learning and Data Analytics, which are typically categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The focus of the paper is on parallel and asynchronous optimization, which falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also proposes a new framework for adapting the step size in an online fashion, which involves modeling the staleness distribution, and hence could be categorized under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
